'''Gay Doctors Ireland''' ('''GDI''') is an organisation of gay, lesbian, bisexual and transgender ([[LGBT]]) physicians and medical students in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. It was founded in 2010 as Ireland's first association for LGBT doctors.<ref name=IT>{{Cite news |work=Irish Times |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/health/2010/0427/1224269149408.html |date=April 4, 2010 |title=Gay and lesbian doctors find a voice |first=Michelle |last=McDonagh |access-date=2010-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020214920/http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/health/2010/0427/1224269149408.html |archive-date=2012-10-20 |dead-url=no |df= }} Full version on GDI website here [http://www.gaydoctorsireland.ie/news?start=6] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721124725/http://www.gaydoctorsireland.ie/news?start=6 |date=2011-07-21 }}.</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.imt.ie/opinion/2010/04/changing_conservative_views.html |work=[[Irish Medical Times]] |title=Changing conservative views |first2=Aoife |last2=Connors |first=Terence |last=Cosgrave |date=April 28, 2010 |access-date=2010-04-29 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120802115603/http://www.imt.ie/opinion/2010/04/changing_conservative_views.html |archive-date=2012-08-02 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
==Purpose== GDI is an educational, professional and social support network for LGBT doctors and medical students. The group's inaugural [[annual general meeting]] featured [[Jesse Ehrenfeld|Doctor Jesse Ehrenfeld]] of [[Harvard University]].<ref name=IT/><ref>{{Cite news |work=Medical Independent |url=http://medicalindependent.ie/page.aspx?title=first_irish_gay_doctors_agm |date=April 15, 2010 |title=First Irish gay doctors AGM |first=Pat |last=Kelly |access-date=2010-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721125319/http://medicalindependent.ie/page.aspx?title=first_irish_gay_doctors_agm |archive-date=2011-07-21 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |work=Irish Medical News |url=http://imn.ie/index.php/current-issue/interview/3468-making-medicine-more-inclusive |title=Making medicine more inclusive |first=Lloyd |last=Mudiwa |date=May 4, 2010 }}{{Dead link|date=June 2011 }} (copy on GDI website here [http://www.gaydoctorsireland.ie/news?start=3] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721124717/http://www.gaydoctorsireland.ie/news?start=3 |date=2011-07-21 }})</ref>
==Activities== Among the issues addressed by the group is the [[Irish Blood Transfusion Service]] controversial [[Irish Blood Transfusion Service#Gay blood ban|ban on gay men donating blood]].<ref>{{Cite news |work=Irish Medical News |date=May 4, 2010 |url=http://imn.ie/index.php/news/3461-gay-doctors-ireland-criticise-blood-transfusion-ban |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130521110619/http://imn.ie/index.php/news/3461-gay-doctors-ireland-criticise-blood-transfusion-ban |dead-url=yes |archive-date=May 21, 2013 |first=Lloyd |last=Mudiwa |title=Gay Doctors Ireland criticise blood transfusion ban |quote=The interim Chairman of Gay Doctors Ireland (GDI) has said the IBTS (Irish Blood Transfusion Service) policy of refusing blood donations from gay men is "unscientific" and outdated.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Author Ethan Troy-Barnes |url=http://www.universityobserver.ie/2011/10/04/flesh-and-blood/ |title=Flesh and Blood - University Observer |publisher=Universityobserver.ie |date=2011-10-04 |accessdate=2014-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022131931/http://www.universityobserver.ie/2011/10/04/flesh-and-blood/ |archive-date=2014-10-22 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> In September 2011, GDI criticised [[Brian Walsh (Irish politician)|Deputy Brian Walsh's]] efforts to deny [[Sex reassignment surgery|surgery]] to transgender patients.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://medicalindependent.ie/page.aspx?title=gay_doctors_ireland_slams_tds_comments | title=Archived copy | access-date=2011-09-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001062922/http://www.medicalindependent.ie/page.aspx?title=gay_doctors_ireland_slams_tds_comments# | archive-date=2011-10-01 | dead-url=bot: unknown | df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2011/0914/1224304082329.html | work=The Irish Times | first=Fiona | last=Gartland | title=State paid for 14 sex-change operations over five years | date=September 14, 2011 | access-date=2011-09-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110914132655/http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2011/0914/1224304082329.html | archive-date=2011-09-14 | dead-url=no | df= }}</ref>
In April 2011, GDI announced an annual LGBT Health Research Bursary for medical students, the first of its kind in Ireland.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://medicalindependent.ie/page.aspx?title=first_lgbt_health_bursary_announced |first=James |last=Fogarty |title=First LGBT health bursary announced |work=Medical Independent |date=April 21, 2011 |access-date=2011-04-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110821161440/http://medicalindependent.ie/page.aspx?title=first_lgbt_health_bursary_announced |archive-date=2011-08-21 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref>
