{{infobox ethnic group| |group = Karagash |native_name = карагаш-ногайлар |image = File:Kundrof Tatar Turkoman of Astrakhan Mongoloid Caucasoid Eurasian.png | image_caption = "Kundrof Tatar" (Karagash Noghay) 1906 |population= ca. 7,000 - 8,000 |popplace= ([[Russia]]) |region1 = {{flag|Russia}} |pop1 = 7,000 (2008) |ref1 = |region2 = |pop2 = |ref2 = |rels = [[Sunni Islam]] |langs = [[Nogai language]] |related = [[Astrakhan Tatars]], [[Nogais|Nogay]] }}
The '''Karagash''' (or as they call themselves, '''Qaragashly''', and '''Qaragash-nogailar''') are one of the ethnic [[Nogais|Nogay]] groups that live in the vicinity of [[Astrakhan]], [[Russia]]. They are one of the two groups designated as the [[Astrakhan Tatars]]. The largest Karagash settlement is the town of [[Rastopulovka]].
